author: @Gammys-interests
text:
Other than the fact that they didn’t struggle from a small company, their story aligns so closely with BTS: the continued barrage of undeserved hate, their names aligning to powerfully with what they would have to be (Bulletproof and Fearless), their fandom names -BTS has a ARMY standing behind them and along side them, while Le Sserafim has a bunch of FeatNots always remind them to be fearless.  MOST importantly, they both rose above, only spread positivity and are fierce battlers for themselves and their careers. 

I am ARMY and baby FearNot.  They are the only two KPop groups I listen to. I do add Illit in some because I do like them and I want to support them, too, but I can’t recognize them by name, etc. like I can with LSF.
